(305, 1, '2023-04-18 20:22:33', '2023-04-18 20:22:33', 'If the pagination is not showing up after adding the code, there could be a few reasons why. Here are a few things to check:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Check if the custom post type has enough posts to require pagination. If there are less than the <code>posts_per_page</code> number of posts, pagination will not be necessary.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure that the <code>paged</code> query variable is being correctly passed to the WP_Query function. You can check this by adding <code>echo $paged;</code> to the code after the <code>$paged = get_query_var(\'paged\') ? get_query_var(\'paged\') : 1;</code> line. If the output is not the current page number, then there may be an issue with how the query variable is being passed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Make sure that the <code>paginate_links()</code> function is being called within the main loop. If it is outside of the loop, it will not display the correct pagination links.</li>\r\n 	<li>Check if there are any conflicting plugins or themes that may be interfering with the pagination. Try disabling plugins one-by-one to see if any of them are causing the issue.</li>\r\n 	<li>If none of the above solutions work, try using a different pagination plugin or creating a custom pagination function.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Demo', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'demo', '', '', '2023-04-18 20:22:33', '2023-04-18 20:22:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/learncustom/?post_type=mypractices&#038;p=305', 0, 'mypractices', '', 0),
(306, 1, '2023-04-18 20:22:33', '2023-04-18 20:22:33', 'If the pagination is not showing up after adding the code, there could be a few reasons why. Here are a few things to check:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Check if the custom post type has enough posts to require pagination. If there are less than the <code>posts_per_page</code> number of posts, pagination will not be necessary.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure that the <code>paged</code> query variable is being correctly passed to the WP_Query function. You can check this by adding <code>echo $paged;</code> to the code after the <code>$paged = get_query_var(\'paged\') ? get_query_var(\'paged\') : 1;</code> line. If the output is not the current page number, then there may be an issue with how the query variable is being passed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Make sure that the <code>paginate_links()</code> function is being called within the main loop. If it is outside of the loop, it will not display the correct pagination links.</li>\r\n 	<li>Check if there are any conflicting plugins or themes that may be interfering with the pagination. Try disabling plugins one-by-one to see if any of them are causing the issue.</li>\r\n 	<li>If none of the above solutions work, try using a different pagination plugin or creating a custom pagination function.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Demo', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '305-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-04-18 20:22:33', '2023-04-18 20:22:33', '', 305, 'http://localhost/learncustom/?p=306', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(307, 1, '2023-04-18 21:44:39', '2023-04-18 21:44:39', 'How to add custom pagination on this code &lt;?php\r\n// Template Name: Practices\r\nget_header();\r\n\r\n$args = array(\r\n\'post_type\' =&gt; \'mypractices\',\r\n\'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 4,\r\n);\r\n?&gt;\r\n&lt;div id=\"contents\"&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=\"clearfix\"&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=\"sidebar\"&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;?php the_title(); ?&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;?php dynamic_sidebar(\'practice_sidebar\'); ?&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n&lt;?php dynamic_sidebar(\'testimonials\'); ?&gt;\r\n&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=\"main\"&gt;\r\n&lt;h1&gt;&lt;?php the_title(); ?&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n&lt;?php the_content(); ?&gt;\r\n&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul class=\"practices\"&gt;\r\n&lt;?php\r\n// Build Query to fetch 6 news post types\r\n// $args = array(\r\n// \'post_type\' =&gt; \'mypractices\',\r\n// \'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 4,\r\n// );\r\n$custom_query = new WP_Query( $args );\r\n\r\n// The Loop\r\nif ( $custom_query-&gt;have_posts() ) {\r\nwhile ( $custom_query-&gt;have_posts() ) {\r\n$custom_query-&gt;the_post();\r\n\r\n?&gt;\r\n&lt;li class=\"frame5\"&gt;\r\n&lt;?php $featured_img_url = get_the_post_thumbnail_url(get_the_ID(),\'full\');?&gt;\r\n&lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?&gt;\" class=\"box\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"&lt;?php echo $featured_img_url ?&gt;\" height=\"198\" width=\"265\"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;?php the_title(); ?&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;?php }\r\n\r\n} else {\r\n// no posts found\r\n}\r\n/* Restore original Post Data */\r\nwp_reset_postdata(); ?&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;!-- Start Get Daynamic Footer --&gt;\r\n&lt;?php get_footer(); ?&gt;\r\n\r\n<strong>To add custom pagination to your code, you can modify it as follows:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Get Code by ChatGTP for pagination</strong>\r\n\r\n&lt;?php\r\n// Template N